==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hopefully
<hw>Hope"ful*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
hopeful manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>I hope; if all goes well; <as>as,
<ex>hopefully</ex>, the dress will be ready before the party</as>.</def>
<note>Some prescriptivists object to this usage as being ungrammatical,
but it is very common and well understood. It is usually used to begin a
sentence describing a desired future event.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hopeite</ent>⟦br⟧
